&lt;p class=MsoNormal align=center style='text-align:center'>&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p>
&lt;p class=MsoNormal align=center style='text-align:center'>&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p>
&lt;p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt'>What
We Learn from Experience&lt;/span>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt'>&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt'>            When
Peter came to Joppa that day, they began showing him the garments and coats
Dorcas had made. I venture to say, they did not do that because the garments
were &lt;u>nicely made&lt;/u>, although no doubt they were. I venture to say, they
did not do that because she was a &lt;u>good seamstress&lt;/u>, although she probably
was. I venture to say, they did not do that because the garments were &lt;u>expensive&lt;/u>,
although she may have used the best material she could find.&lt;/span>&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>THE PASSING OF JAIRUS’ DAUGHTER</title><link>https://christir.org/essays/ministry/sermons/funerals/the-passing-of-jairus-daughter/</link><pubDate>Mon, 16 Feb 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://christir.org/essays/ministry/sermons/funerals/the-passing-of-jairus-daughter/</guid><description>&lt;style>
